headline: CDW (CDW) Leans on AI, Cloud and Buybacks: What Story Do Record Margins Really Tell?
summary: CDW Corporation recently reported fourth-quarter 2025 results, with sales rising to US$5,511 million and net income reaching US$279.5 million, while its Board declared a quarterly dividend of US$0.630 per share payable on March 10, 2026. The quarter was marked by growth in AI, cloud, and professional services that lifted gross margins to their highest level of the year and underpinned nearly US$1 billion returned to shareholders through dividends and buybacks in 2025. headline: CDW Q4 Deep Dive: Cloud, AI Services, and End-Market Diversity Drive Outperformance
summary: IT solutions provider CDW (NASDAQGS:CDW) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 6.3% year on year to $5.51 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.57 per share was 5.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: CDW Earnings Beat Highlights Cloud And AI Growth Plus Higher Dividend
summary: CDW (NasdaqGS:CDW) reported strong fourth quarter and full year results, with sales and profit performance ahead of earlier expectations. The company highlighted demand for software, cloud, professional services and AI focused solutions as key contributors to the period’s performance. The Board approved a higher quarterly dividend, extending CDW’s pattern of returning cash to shareholders.
